cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with graph colouring and forbidden subgraphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a linear time recognition algorithm.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as cographs are a class of graphs that have applications in computational geometry.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as graph colouring has applications in game theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the problem of ($P_3$-free, $K_3$-free)-colouring is known to be NP-complete.
